de.ityx.mediatrix.data

Class Attachment

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ityx.mediatrix.data.ErpsData
      • de.ityx.mediatrix.data.Attachment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAttachment, IContent, IErpsData, Serializable

    public class Attachment
extends ErpsData
implements IContent, IAttachment
    An attachment is a file which is sent in the body of a customer mail, answer or service center question. How to use: Question question = new Question(); Attachment att = new Attachment(); att. setClientFilename("test.txt"); attachment1.setBuffer(getBytes()); question.addAttachment(att); API.getClientAPI().getQuestionAPI().store(question); At the server side(e.g. in the service) the attachments must be stored extra: API.getServerAPI().getAttachmentAPI().store(att);
    See Also:

      • setEmbedded

        public void setEmbedded(boolean embedded)
        Explicitly sets an attachment to be regarded as an embedded one.
        Note: This setter manipulates the embedded option for an attachment only during its object-lifecycle and is not being persisted in the db. Any new attachment object would decide if it is embedded or not only via the conditions in isEmbedded().
